<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-46-0794 </DOCNO><TEXT>As the fundamental knowledge for understanding the situations of coalin Japan, characteristic points were explained that total consumptionamounted to 110 million tons, among which 90 million tons were importedand that 60% of the total consumption was consumed by the productionof coke, only 1/3 of which was shared by domestic source. Basic knowledgeof coal science was summarized such as creation process of coal, worlddistribution of resources, estimated amount of deposit with obtainablelimit by tables, classification of coal with its properties. In addition,application technology and trend of demand werementioned. (5 figs, 8tabs)</TEXT></DOC>